column1: Atmospheric Delta-14C (permil) derived from flask air samples

Source: H. D. Graven, R. F. Keeling, A. F. Bollenbacher
These data are subject to revision based on recalibration of standard gases. Questions
about the data should be directed to Dr. Heather Graven (hgraven@ucsd.edu)
and Dr. Ralph Keeling (rkeeling@ucsd.edu), Scripps CO2 Program.
Flask data in this file last updated 23-Apr-2010

in CO2 at seven global sampling sites in the Scripps flask network: Analysis of
spatial gradients and seasonal cycles. Journal of Geophysical Research,
Reported are age- and d13C-corrected ratios, in reference to the Modern Standard,
defined as Delta" in M. Stuiver and H.A. Polach
